This package implements CVaR / leximin reductions as a plugin for
fairlearn (MIT License, https://github.com/fairlearn/fairlearn).
The reductions API design follows Agarwal et al. (2018), "A Reductions
Approach to Fair Classification," ICML.

Philosophical framing acknowledges:
- John Rawls, "A Theory of Justice" (1971), as the principal inspiration
  for maximin / leximin / difference-principle aggregation.
- Amartya Sen, "Equality of What?" (1979) and "The Idea of Justice" (2009),
  whose capability-approach critique of primary goods this project
  acknowledges as a legitimate constraint on Rawlsian framings (see README).
